tlet Development</li>         <li>Portlet Deployment</li>         <li>Service Builder</li>     </ul>     </li>     <li><strong>Blog Improvements</strong>     <ul>         <li>RSS Feed</li>         <li>User / Guest Comments</li>         <li>Browsable Categories</li>         <li>Tags / Labels</li>         <li>Entry Rating System</li>     </ul>     </li>     <li><strong>Wiki File Attachments</strong></li>     <li><strong>Applicaton Servers</strong>     <ul>         <li>Glassfish</li>     </ul>     </li>     <li><strong>Liferay Vision - Business Intelligence Suite</strong></li>     <li><strong>Liferay University - Learning Management System</strong></li>     <li><strong>Liferay Mesh - TBD</strong></li> </ul>', 'general', '', '', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20060704230100, TRUE, 'liferay.com.1', 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE);
insert into JournalArticle (companyId, groupId, articleId, version, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired) values ('liferay.com', 1, 'DEVZONE-GLOSSARY', 1.0, 'liferay.com.1', 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'Devzone - Glossary', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US,es_ES\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"textarea\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\"><![CDATA[<table boder=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"15\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\"><b>Term</b></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"90%\"><b>Definition</b></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">CMS</td><td valign=\"top\">Content Management\nSystem. System used to allow the non-technical writer to easily produce\nand present material on a web page. The CMS technology developed in\nLiferay is also known as the <a href=\"@friendly_url_public@/guest/products/journal\" _fcksavedurl=\"@friendly_url_public@/guest/products/journal\">Liferay\nJournal</a>.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">JSR-168</td><td valign=\"top\">A Java\nCommunity Process (JCP) standard specification for the interoperability\nbetween Portlets and Portals. See <a href=\"http://www.jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=168\" _fcksavedurl=\"http://www.jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=168\">spec</a>.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">JSR-170</td><td valign=\"top\">A Java\nCommunity Process (JCP) standard specification for a repository of\ncontent used by the CMS. See <a href=\"http://www.jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=170\" _fcksavedurl=\"http://www.jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=170\">spec</a>.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">Liferay Journal</td><td valign=\"top\">Liferay\'s CMS <a href=\"@friendly_url_public@/guest/products/journal\" _fcksavedurl=\"@friendly_url_public@/guest/products/journal\">product</a>.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">Liferay Portal Enterprise</td><td valign=\"top\">JSR-168 portal that supports EJBs. The code is\nidentical with Liferay Portal\nProfessional.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">Liferay Portal Professional</td><td valign=\"top\">JSR-168 portal that does not support EJBs. The code is\nidentical with Liferay Portal\nEnterprise.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">Portal</td><td valign=\"top\">A website that\nshares information and enables collaboration of its users through the\nuse of its portlets. Liferay Portal has been used by businesses,\nschools, non-profit organizations, and many others. See their <a href=\"@friendly_url_public@/guest/stories\" _fcksavedurl=\"@friendly_url_public@/guest/stories\">stories</a>.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">Portlet</td><td valign=\"top\">A portal-based\napplication that supports autonomous functionality. Liferay Portal\nships with over 50 useful, pre-bundled\nportlets.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">Theme</td><td valign=\"top\">Flexibility to\nchange the look and feel of a given page or site with the click of a\nbutton.&nbsp; The Liferay community has contributed dozens of\nthemes that range from clean and professional appearances to fun and\nwacky. See <a href=\"@friendly_url_public@/guest/downloads/themes\" _fcksavedurl=\"@friendly_url_public@/guest/downloads/themes\">contributions</a>.</td></tr></tbody></table>]]></dynamic-content>\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"es_ES\"><![CDATA[<table boder=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"15\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\"><b>Term</b></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"90%\"><b>Definition</b></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">CMS</td><td valign=\"top\">Content Management System. (Sistema de gestión de contenidos) Es un sistema orientado a permitir a perfiles no técnicos producir y presentar material en una página web. El CMS desarrollado en Liferay es conocido con el nombre <a _fcksavedurl=\"http://www.liferay.com/web/guest/products/journal\" href=\"http://www.liferay.com/web/guest/products/journal\">Liferay Journal o Diario</a>.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">JSR-168</td><td valign=\"top\">Un estándar del Java Community Process (JCP) que especifica la interoperabilidades entre Portlets y Portales. Ver <a _fcksavedurl=\"http://www.jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=168\" href=\"http://www.jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=168\">la specificación</a>.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">JSR-170</td><td valign=\"top\">Un estándar del Java Community Process (JCP) que define las características y API de un repositorio de contenidos que podría ser usado por un CMS. Ver <a _fcksavedurl=\"http://www.jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=170\" href=\"http://www.jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=170\">la specificación</a>.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">Liferay Journal</td><td valign=\"top\">El CMS de Liferay. En español se traduce habitualmente como el <a _fcksavedurl=\"http://www.liferay.com/web/guest/products/journal\" href=\"http://www.liferay.com/web/guest/products/journal\">diario</a>.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">Liferay Portal Enterprise</td><td valign=\"top\">Portal JSR-168 que soporta EJBs. El código es idéntico al de Liferay Portal Professional.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">Liferay Portal Professional</td><td valign=\"top\">Portal JSR-168 que soporta EJBs. El código es idéntico al de Liferay Portal Enterprise.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">Portal</td><td valign=\"top\">Un sitio web que comparte información y permite la colaboración entre sus usuarios mediante sus portlets. Liferay Portal ha sido usado por negocios, colegios, organizaciones sin ánimo de lucro y muchos otros. Lea nuestros <a _fcksavedurl=\"http://www.liferay.com/web/guest/stories\" href=\"http://www.liferay.com/web/guest/stories\">casos de éxito.</a></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">Portlet</td><td valign=\"top\">Una aplicación de portal que puede funcionar autónomamente. Liferay Portal incluye unos 50 portlets listos para ser usados.</td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">Theme</td><td valign=\"top\">Flexibilidad para cambiar la apariencia de una página o sitio web completo con una simple pulsación del ratón. La comunidad de liferay ha contribuido un gran número de temas (themes) que presentan apariencias diversas desde algunas limpias y profesionales hasta otras divertidas o informales. Vea las <a _fcksavedurl=\"http://www.liferay.com/web/guest/downloads/themes\" href=\"http://www.liferay.com/web/guest/downloads/themes\">contribuciones</a>.</td></tr></tbody></table>]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-TEXT', 'BASIC-TEXT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20060606175200, TRUE, 'liferay.com.1', 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE);
