content components previously created.<br><br><b>Resolution</b><br><br>With all its prebundled portlets, Liferay Portal was decidely the best candidate. These portlets&nbsp;allowed the user of the \"Digital Magazine\" to have visual tools for editing their content. Through the CMS, the portal already had tools that separated editing and managing content. Additionally, it was easy to visually apply various layout templates to different parts of the \"Digital Magazine.\"<br><br>Thanks to these portlets, the \"Digital Magazine\" is now an active section of the <i>Educacyl</i> portal. It has a professional look-and-feel yet is easy to use by non-technical people.</div>]]></dynamic-content>\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"es_ES\"><![CDATA[<div><b>Perfil de la Compañía</b><br><br>Castilla y León es una de las regiones más grandes de España.<br><br><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">El Reto</span><b></b><br><br>La Junta de Castilla-León quería una “Revista Digital? en la que publicar información para su portal educativo, Educacyl. Pero había un obstáculo: la “Revista Digital? necesitaba estar orientada a usuarios no-técnicos que dividirían la creación de contenidos en dos partes. La primera parte permitiría a los usuarios crear el contenido para ser mostrado en el portal. La segunda parte debía ser una herramienta que permitiese a los usuarios componer la estructura de la web con los componentes creados con anterioridad.<br><br>La SoluciónCon todos los portlets proporcionados, Liferay Portal era, decididamente el mejor candidato. Estos portlets permitieron a los usuarios de la “Revista Digital? tener herramientas visuales para editar sus contenidos. Gracias al CMS, el portal ya tenía herramientas para editar y gestionar por separado los contenidos. Además, fue sencillo aplicar visualmente varias plantillas de distribuciones a diferentes partes de la “Revista Digital?.<br><br>Gracias a esos portlets, la “Revista Digital? es ahora una sección muy activa del portal Educacyl. Tiene una apariencia profesional, a pesar de que es fácil de utilizar por parte de personal no técnico.</div>]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-1\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-JUNTA.screenshot-thumbnail-1.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-1\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-JUNTA.screenshot-full-1.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-2\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-JUNTA.screenshot-thumbnail-2.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-2\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-JUNTA.screenshot-full-2.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-3\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-JUNTA.screenshot-thumbnail-3.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-3\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-JUNTA.screenshot-full-3.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-4\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-4\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-5\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-5\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-6\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-6\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-7\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-7\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-8\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-8\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-9\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-9\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-10\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-10\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-SHOWCASE', 'BASIC-SHOWCASE', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20060501180200, TRUE, 'liferay.com.1', 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE);
insert into JournalArticle (companyId, groupId, articleId, version, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired) values ('liferay.com', 1, 'STORIES-KOSICE-AIRPORT', 1.0, 'liferay.com.1', 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'Stories Kosice Airport', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US,es_ES\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content-title\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[Košice Airport]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"logo-image\" type=\"image\">\n    <dynamic-content id=\"liferay.com.journal.article.1.STORIES-KOSICE-AIRPORT.logo-image.1.0\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1.STORIES-KOSICE-AIRPORT.logo-image&amp;version=1.0</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"company-link\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[www.airportkosice.sk]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"quote\" type=\"text_box\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\"><![CDATA[&quot;The portal system is an excellent tool. It provides stable connectivity of our internal systems with Internet, allowing us to supply passengers with up-to-date and reliable information on line. We also appreciate practically limitless number of portlets and easy to use administration interface.&quot; – Ing. Ján Palko – Operations and Business Manager]]></dynamic-content>\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"es_ES\"><![CDATA[&quot;El sistema de portal es una excelente herramienta. Proporciona una conectividad estable a nuestros sistemas internos desde Internet, permitiéndonos proporcionar a los pasajeros información actualizada y fiable. También apreciamos el prácticamente ilimitado número de portlets y la facilidad de uso de la interfaz de administración.&quot; – Ing. Ján Palko – Operations and Business Manager]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"main-text\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\"><![CDATA[<div>\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Company Profile</span>\n<br><br>Košice Airport was built in 1951 near the city of Košice, Slovak Republic, and has been growing ever since. In December 2004 Košice Airport became a civil international airport. By the end of the same year, the airport succeeded in opening a new T2 terminal.  In the summer of 2005, it received a “Construction of the Year? award at the 11th National public contest.  Košice Airport has also recently exceeded the record for the number of handled passengers. In January 2006 the TwoOne consortium has been recommended to the Slovak cabinet as the winner of a tender for 66-percent stakes in Bratislava and Košice airports. Investments in Košice airport should exceed €24 million by the end of 2015.\n<br><br>\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Challenge</span><br><br>Košice Airport management was primarily seeking a new attractive web site. But after seeing the power a web portal delivers in connectivity between the Internet and the company Intranet, the management instantly changed their minds. Although the project was limited by a modest budget, the Airport managed to gain a sufficient grant from the Ministry of transportation, posts, and telecommunications. The basic requirements included a user friendly environment, ease in administration, display of up-to-date information (e.g. arrivals and departures, weather, statistics, etc.), and a modern design. Košice Airport hoped to get an attractive Internet presentation and effective intranet system, both connected in an interactive application.</div>\n<div><br><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Resolution</span><br><br>The delivery of a custom portal system exceeded the expectations of Košice Airport. Many services were provided building on top of the Liferay Portal:<br></div>\n<ul>\n<li>Layout of tree structures<br></li>\n<li>Full screen resolution layout</li>\n<li>Improved Journal portlet</li>\n<ul>\n<li>Full support of UTF8 for templates and structures</li>\n<li>Managing article discussions</li>\n<li>Counters for most read or discussed articles</li>\n<li>Assigning articles various categories for layouts</li>\n<li>Image thumbnails for articles</li>\n<li>Journal article with embedded Flash animations</li>\n<li>Access to remote services using a proxy</li>\n<li>Real-time display of arrivals/departures from external systems</li>\n<li>English version</li>\n</ul></ul><div>Coming soon:<br></div>\n<ul>\n<li>Airport statistics</li>\n</ul>]]></dynamic-content>\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"es_ES\"><![CDATA[<div>\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Perfil de la Compañía</span><br><br>El aeropuerto de Košice se construyó en 1951 cerca de la ciudad de Košice, República Eslovaca, y ha estado creciendo desde entonces. En diciembre de 2004, el aeropuerto de Košice se convirtió en aeropuerto civil internacional. Al final de ese mismo año, el aeropuerto inauguró con éxito una nueva terminal T2. En el verano de 2005, recibió el premio “Construction of the Year? en el 11º concurso público Nacional. El aeropuerto Košice también ha superado recientemente la marca de número de viajeros. En enero de 2006, el consorcio TwoOne ha sido recomendado al consejo de ministros eslovaco como ganador de un concurso público por el 66 por ciento de las inversiones de los aeropuertos de Bratislava y Košice. Las inversiones en el aeropuerto de Košice podrían superar los 24 millones de euros hacia el final de 2015.<br><br>\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">El Reto</span><br><br>Los gestores del aeropuerto de Košice buscaban, principalmente un nuevo y atractivo web. Pero, tras observar la potencia que un portal web proporciona en cuanto a la conectividad entre Internet y la Intranet de la compaía, la gerencia instantáneamente cambió de opinión. A pesar de que el proyecto estaba limitado por un presupuesto modesto, el aeropuerto realizó las gestiones necesarias para obtener las subvenciones necesarias por parte del Ministerio de Transportes, Correos y Telecomunicaciones. Los requisitos básicos incluían un entorno amigable para el usuario, sencillez de administración, capacidad de mostrar información actualizada (p.e. llegadas y salidas, tiempo, estadísticas, etc.) y un diseño moderno. El aeropuerto de Košice buscaba conseguir una presencia en Internet atractiva y un sistema de intranet efectivo, ambos conectados en una aplicación interactiva.</div>\n<div><br><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">La Solución</span><br><br>La entrega del sistema de portal adaptado superó las expectativas del aeropuerto de Košice. Muchos de los servicios se proveyeron sobre los servicios ofrecidos por el Portal Liferay:<br></div>\n<ul>\n<li>Distribución en tres columnas<br></li>\n<li>Distribución en pantalla completa</li>\n<li>•&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Portlet Diario mejorado</li>\n<ul>\n<li>Soporte completo de UTF8 para plantillas y estructuras</li>\n<li>Gestión de discusiones sobre artículos</li>\n<li>Contadores para los artículos más leídos o comentados</li>\n<li>Posibilidad de asignar varias categorías a un artículo</li>\n<li>Miniaturas de imágenes para los artículos</li>\n<li>Artículo de Diario con animaciones Flash incrustadas</li>\n<li>Acceso a servicios remotos mediante proxy</li>\n<li>Presentación en tiempo real de llegadas y salidas desde sistemas externos</li>\n<li>Versión en inglés</li>\n</ul></ul><div>En breve:<br></div>\n<ul>\n<li>Estadísticas del aeropuerto</li>\n</ul>]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-1\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-KOSICE-AIRPORT.screenshot-thumbnail-1.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-1\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-KOSICE-AIRPORT.screenshot-full-1.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-2\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-KOSICE-AIRPORT.screenshot-thumbnail-2.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-2\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-KOSICE-AIRPORT.screenshot-full-2.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-3\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-KOSICE-AIRPORT.screenshot-thumbnail-3.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-3\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-KOSICE-AIRPORT.screenshot-full-3.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-4\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-KOSICE-AIRPORT.screenshot-thumbnail-4.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-4\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-KOSICE-AIRPORT.screenshot-full-4.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-5\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-5\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-6\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-6\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-7\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-7\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-8\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-8\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-9\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-9\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-10\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-10\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"title\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[Košice Airport]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"subtitle\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-SHOWCASE', 'BASIC-SHOWCASE', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20060501180200, TRUE, 'liferay.com.1', 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE);
insert into JournalArticle (companyId, groupId, articleId, version, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired) values ('liferay.com', 1, 'STORIES-MFK-KOSICE', 1.0, 'liferay.com.1', 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'Stories MFK Kosice', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n\n<root>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content-title\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[MFK Košice]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"logo-image\" type=\"image\">\n    <dynamic-content id=\"liferay.com.journal.article.1.STORIES-MFK-KOSICE.logo-image.1.0\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1.STORIES-MFK-KOSICE.logo-image&amp;version=1.0</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"company-link\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[www.mfkkosice.sk]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"quote\" type=\"text_box\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[&quot;My intention is to build up a respectable football club that will follow a professional path from the very beginning. To achieve that, it is essential to attract fans and to offer them to become an important part of the club structures. I realize that our on line presentation represents an interactive contact of the club with its supporters; it is our noticeboard and a mirror of our achievements. The feedback of the portal content design we are getting assures us of the right direction we have taken.&quot; - Blažej Podolák – club president]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"main-text\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[<DIV><SPAN style=\"FONT-WEIGHT: bold\">Company Profile</SPAN><BR><BR>MFK Košice started a new era of football (soccer) in the city of Košice, Slovak republic in the summer of 2005. Football has been a tradition in Košice for more than 50 years.&nbsp; Many remember the city\'s participation in a group stage of the Champions League during the 97-98 season.&nbsp; Then, for the last three years the city has not had a football team in the first two divisions of the Slovak league. MFK Košice, a football club newly founded by the company STEEL TRANS and the city of Košice, was to bring back the times of honor and glory for the players and the fans. Although MFK Košice started out in Division II, the team management has daring plans to advance to Division I by next season and to build up a respectable European football team within the next few years.<BR><BR><SPAN style=\"FONT-WEIGHT: bold\">Challenge</SPAN><BR><BR>Football club MFK Košice needed an attractive on-line presentation with game statistics, club info, e-shop, and other popular interactive features for fans, press and sponsors. Since the feedback from fans is the key element for every sports club, MFK Košice requested on-line discussions, forums, questionnaires, image galleries, and a clean administration interface.&nbsp; The site would bring fresh news about games, press conferences, and other club events without any extra programming or special IT skills. MFK Košice expects to become a successful team.&nbsp; This growth potential calls for an upgradeable system that does not need to be rebuilt frequently.<BR><BR><SPAN style=\"FONT-WEIGHT: bold\">Resolution</SPAN><BR style=\"FONT-WEIGHT: bold\"><BR>The portal for MFK Košice was the solution, built on a customized Liferay Portal featuring:<BR>\n<UL>\n<LI>Layout tree structures</LI>\n<LI>Full screen resolution layout</LI>\n<LI>Dynamic (JS) menu system</LI>\n<LI>Improved journal portlet</LI>\n<UL>\n<LI>Full support of UTF8 for templates and structures</LI>\n<LI>Managing article discussions</LI>\n<LI>Counters for most read or discussed articles</LI>\n<LI>Assigning articles various categories for layouts</LI>\n<LI>Image thumbnails for articles</LI>\n<LI>Journal article with embedded Flash animations</LI></UL>\n<LI>Players/team/league (PTL) statistic system</LI>\n<LI>Anonymous access to document library files</LI>\n<LI>Anonymous/guest access message board</LI></UL><SPAN style=\"FONT-WEIGHT: bold\">Coming soon:</SPAN><BR>\n<UL>\n<LI>Chat</LI>\n<LI>Shopping</LI>\n<LI>Improved image gallery</LI>\n<LI>New version of players/team/league statistic system</LI></UL></DIV>]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-1\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/image/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-MFK-KOSICE.screenshot-thumbnail-1.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-1\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/image/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-MFK-KOSICE.screenshot-full-1.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-2\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/image/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-MFK-KOSICE.screenshot-thumbnail-2.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-2\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/image/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-MFK-KOSICE.screenshot-full-2.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-3\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/image/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-MFK-KOSICE.screenshot-thumbnail-3.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-3\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/image/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-MFK-KOSICE.screenshot-full-3.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-4\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/image/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-MFK-KOSICE.screenshot-thumbnail-4.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-4\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/image/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-MFK-KOSICE.screenshot-full-4.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-5\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-5\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-6\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-6\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-7\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-7\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-8\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-8\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-9\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-9\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-10\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-10\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"title\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[MFK Košice]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"subtitle\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-SHOWCASE', 'BASIC-SHOWCASE', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20060501180239, TRUE, 'liferay.com.1', 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE);
insert into JournalArticle (companyId, groupId, articleId, version, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired) values ('liferay.com', 1, 'STORIES-OAKWOOD', 1.0, 'liferay.com.1', 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, 'Stories Oakwood', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US,es_ES\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content-title\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[Oakwood]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"logo-image\" type=\"image\">\n    <dynamic-content id=\"liferay.com.journal.article.1.STORIES-OAKWOOD.logo-image.1.0\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1.STORIES-OAKWOOD.logo-image&amp;version=1.0</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"company-link\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[www.oakwood.com]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"quote\" type=\"text_box\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\"><![CDATA[&quot;Our view is that a portal is fundamentally an application integration tool rather than a solution in and of itself, so we were intent on applying our program costs to rapid customization, not license fees. This turned out to be the right mindset because within a month of initial rollout, our Liferay-based customer portal helped us edge out competitors in several hard-won contracts. Sales people actually started calling HQ to thank the development team.&quot; - Eric Nathanson, Oakwood ]]></dynamic-content>\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"es_ES\"><![CDATA[&quot;Según nuestro punto de vista, un portal es fundamentalmente una herramienta de integración de aplicaciones y no una solución en sí mismo, así es que tratamos de aplicar nuestro programa de costes a una personalización rápida y no a pagos por licencias. Este ha mostrado ser el enfoque correcto ya que en el primer mes, nuestro portal basado en Liferay para clientes nos ha ayudado a vencer a la competencia en varios contratos complicados de ganar. De hecho, nuestra gente de ventas, ha comenzado a llamarnos a la sede central para felicitar al equipo de desarrollo&quot; - Eric Nathanson, Oakwood ]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"main-text\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\"><![CDATA[<div><b>Company Profile</b><br><br>Oakwood Worldwide is the largest temporary housing provider worldwide. With 40 years of multi-family housing experience and 30 years of industry leadership in corporate housing, Oakwood Worldwide is the most experienced leader in temporary furnished apartments. With access to over 400,000 apartments in more than 2,000 U.S. cities, as well as select locations in Canada, Asia, and Europe, 85% of Fortune 500 firms depend on Oakwood Worldwide. <br><br><b>Challenge</b><br><br>To maintain a competitive edge over other housing providers, Oakwood\'s management recognized the need to upgrade their disparate legacy systems. By implementing a more efficient and cost-effective process model, Oakwood hoped to increase profitability and improve the customer\'s ability to book and schedule reservations. With over 400,000 apartments all across the world, Oakwood needed an application that would not only query all availabilities that matched a customer\'s criteria, but&nbsp;would also allow sales agents to effectively meet those requests. <br><br>Oakwood needed the following from an application:\n<ul>\n<li>A Profiles System that would allow sales agents to easily update the properties they are responsible for. </li>\n<li>Content Management System that would manage the layout and content of the website. </li>\n<li>A website with a new look and feel that would improve the customer\'s ability to search and book apartments.</li></ul><b>Resolution</b><br><br>Oakwood Worldwide selected Liferay and its enterprise portal to implement the functionality it needed. By leveraging Liferay Portal Enterprise\'s framework, Liferay implemented the following:\n<ul>\n<li><b>Profiles Portlet</b> - Liferay helped build a Profiles portlet that allowed sales agents to manage properties they were responsible for. This included the ability to upload property images, descriptions, and other information that would help a sales agent in closing a sale. </li>\n<li><b>XSLT CMS</b> - Oakwood\'s website is driven by Liferay\'s Content Management System. Via an XSLT templating system, Oakwood can control the content displayed on the site along with its layout. </li>\n<li><b>eInvoicing</b> -&nbsp; Liferay used web services to integrate a .NET invoicing system into its own portlet within Liferay Portal. </li></ul>As opposed to spending hundreds of thousands of dollars for a commercial application\'s license alone, Oakwood Worldwide saw the advantage of using Liferay\'s open source software to cut costs and build a well architected, long-term solution. </div>]]></dynamic-content>\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"es_ES\"><![CDATA[<div><b>Perfil de la Compañía<br><br></b>Oakwood Worldwide es la mayor compañía de alojamiento temporal del mundo. Con 40 años de experiencia en alojamiento multifamiliar y 30 años de liderazgo en la industria del alojamiento corporativo, Oakwood Worldwide es el líder más experimentado en apartamentos amueblados temporales. Con acceso a cerca de 400.000 apartamentos en más de 2000 ciudades de los USA, además de localidades seleccionadas en Canada, Asia y Europa, el 85% de las firmas del Fortune 500 son clientes nuestros.<br><br><b>El Reto</b><br>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"ES-TRAD\">Para mantener un margen de competitividad\nsobre otros proveedores de alojamiento, la gestión de Oakwood reconoció la\nnecesidad de actualizar sus dispares sistemas propietarios. Implantando un\nmodelo de proceso más eficiente y ajustado a costes, Oakwood tenía la esperanza\nde incrementar los beneficios y mejorar la capacidad de los clientes para\nrealizar y planificar sus reservas. Con alrededor de 400.000 apartamentos en\ntodo el mundo, Oakwood necesitaba una aplicación que no sólo encontrase todos\nlos alojamientos que cumpliesen los criterios de búsqueda del usuario,\nsino<span style=\"\">&nbsp; </span>también los de los agentes de ventas\npara realizar eficientemente esas consultas.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\nOakwood necesitaba una aplicación que cumpliese lo siguiente:\n<ul>\n<li>Un sistema de perfiles que permitiese a los agentes de ventas actualizar fácilmente las propiedades de las que son responsables. </li>\n<li>Un Sistema de Gestión de Contenidos que permitiese gestionar la apariencia y el contenido del sitio web. </li>\n<li>Un sitio web con una apariencia nueva que mejorase la capacidad del cliente para buscar y reservar apartamentos.</li></ul><b>La Solución<br><br></b>Oakwood Worldwide eligió Liferay y su Enterprise Portal para implantar la funcionalidad que necesitaba. Apostando por el entorno Liferay Portal Enterprise, Liferay implementó lo siguiente:\n<ul>\n<li><b>El portlet de perfiles </b>-&nbsp; Liferay ayudó a construir un portlet de perfiles que permitió a los agentes de ventas gestionar propiedades de las que eran responsables. Esto incluyó la capacidad de subir imágenes de la propiedad, descripciones y otra información que ayudaría a un agente de ventas a completar un acuerdo. </li>\n<li><b>XSLT CMS</b> - El sitio web de Oakwood está dirigido por el Sistema de Gestión de Contenido de Liferay. Mediante un sistema de plantillas XSLT, Oakwood puede controlar el contenido mostrado en el sitio además de su apariencia. </li>\n<li><b>eInvoicing</b> -&nbsp; Liferay empleó servicios web para integrar el sistema de facturación implantado con tecnología .NET en su propio portlet dentro de Liferay. </li></ul>En lugar de gastar cientos de miles de dólares sólo en licencias de aplicaciones comerciales, Oakwood Worldwide vio la ventaja de emplear el software open-source de Liferay para recortar gastos y construir una solución bien diseñada y a largo plazo. </div>]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-1\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-OAKWOOD.screenshot-thumbnail-1.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-1\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-OAKWOOD.screenshot-full-1.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-2\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-OAKWOOD.screenshot-thumbnail-2.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-2\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-OAKWOOD.screenshot-full-2.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-3\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-OAKWOOD.screenshot-thumbnail-3.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-3\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-OAKWOOD.screenshot-full-3.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-thumbnail-4\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-OAKWOOD.screenshot-thumbnail-4.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"screenshot-full-4\" type=\"text\">\n    <dynamic-content><![CDATA[content.liferay.com/4.0.0/images/COMPANY-CASE-STUDIES-OAKWOOD.screenshot-full-4.jpg]]></dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n  <dynamic-ele